== Head coaches ==

=== Pre-season changes ===
* In November 2024, prior to the season ending, the North Carolina Tar Heels fired head coach [[Mack Brown]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2024/11/26/sports/north-carolina-fires-mack-brown-after-he-says-he-wants-to-return/|title=North Carolina fires Mack Brown in awkward scene after he says he wants to return|last=Ehalt|first=Matt|website=nypost.com|publisher=The New York Post|date=November 26, 2024|access-date=December 3, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=November 26, 2024 |title=Football Coach Mack Brown Will Not Return After 2024 Season |url=https://goheels.com/news/2024/11/26/carolina-football-coach-mack-brown-will-not-return-after-this-season |access-date=November 26, 2024 |work=University of North Carolina Athletics}}</ref> On December 11, 2024, [[Bill Belichick]] was announced as Brown's replacement.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Florio |first=Mike |author-link=Mike Florio |date=December 13, 2024 |title=Full Bill Belichick contract details emerge |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/nfl/profootballtalk/rumor-mill/news/full-bill-belichick-contract-details-emerge |access-date=December 13, 2024 |website=NBC Sports}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Football Icon Bill Belichick Named Tar Heel Head Coach |url=https://goheels.com/news/2024/12/11/football-icon-bill-belichick-named-north-carolina-head-coach |access-date=December 11, 2024 |work=University of North Carolina Athletics|date=December 11, 2024}}</ref>
* On December 16, 2024, [[Dave Clawson]] resigned as head coach of the Wake Forest Demon Deacons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/43008306/sources-wake-forest-dave-clawson-stepping-coach|title=Wake Forest's Dave Clawson resigns as football coach|work=[[ESPN]]|first=Pete|last=Thamel|date=December 16, 2024|access-date=June 11, 2025}}</ref> [[Jake Dickert]] was hired as his replacement on December 18, 2024.<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Feldman |first1=Bruce |last2=Russo |first2=Ralph D. |date=2024-12-18 |title=Wake Forest hiring Jake Dickert as coach after Dave Clawson's unexpected exit: Sources |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6003493/2024/12/18/jake-dickert-wake-forest-hiring/ |access-date=2024-12-18 |work=[[The Athletic]] |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>
* On March 25, 2025, the Stanford Cardinal fired head coach [[Troy Taylor (American football)|Troy Taylor]] amid an investigation into bullying behavior.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kamrani |first=Christopher |last2=Mandel |first2=Stewart |date=2025-03-25 |title=Stanford fires football coach Troy Taylor following investigations into bullying behavior |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6219705/2025/03/25/stanford-fires-troy-taylor-andrew-luck/ |access-date=2025-03-25 |work=[[The Athletic]] |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> On March 31, 2025, [[Frank Reich]] was hired as interim head coach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gostanford.com/news/2025/03/31/stanford-football-announces-frank-reich-as-interim-head-coach-for-2025-season|title=Stanford football announces Frank Reich as Interim Head Coach for 2025 season|publisher=[[Stanford Cardinal]]|date=March 31, 2025|accessdate=March 31, 2025}}</ref>

